            "question": {
                "text": "Let G be a connected undirected weigthed graph. \nConsider the following two statements. \n\nS1: There exists a minimum weight edge in G which \nis present in every minimum spanning tree of G. \n\nS2: If every edge in G has distinct weight, then G has \na unique minimum spanning treed. \n\nWhich one of the following options is correct?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "S1 is false and S2 is true",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "Both S1 and S2 are flase",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "S1 is true and S2 is false",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "Both S1 and S2 are true.",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "A"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "The Kruskals algorithm can be used to discover the \nMinimum Spanning Tree on a graph G.  \n\n While doing that, we sort the edges according to \ntheir weight and begin choosing the smallest edge.  \n\n Problem with S1: The Kruskals method may not \nalways choose a particular weighted edge if there \nare numerous copies of it. \n\n S2 is True, the Kruskals method will always choose \na distinct set of edges, resulting in a distinct minimal \nspanning tree, if the sorted order of the edges \ncontains only distinct values.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
