            "question": {
                "text": "In a directed acryclic graph with a source vertex s, \nthe qauility-score of a directed path is defined to be \nthe product of the weights of the edges on the path. \n\nFurther, for a vertex v other than s, the quality-score \nof v is defined to be the maximum among the \nquality-scores of all the paths from s to v. the quality \nscore of s is assumed to be 1. \n\n\nThe sum of the quality -scores of all the vertieces in \nthe graph shown above is___.",
