            "question": {
                "text": "In an adjacency list representation of an undirected \nsimple graph G = (V, E), each edge (u, 𝜐) has two \nadjacency list entries: [𝜐] in the adjacency list of u, \nand [u] in the adjacency list of 𝜐. These are called \ntwins of each other. A twin pointer is a pointer from \nan adjacency list entry to its twin. If |E| = m and  \n|V| = n, and the memory size is not a constraint, what \nf \ng \nt\nc \nd \ne\ns \na \nb\n\nis the time complexity of the most efficient algorithm \nto set the twin pointer in each entry in each adjacency \nlist?",
